###############################################################################
# DEM — minimal bootstrap config. `make setup` copies this to .env.
#
# These are the only variables the conductor needs before its database is
# reachable. Everything else — Plane/GitHub/Claude credentials, models,
# notifications — is entered through the admin console's setup wizard and stored
# (encrypted) in the DB. So on a fresh boot the wizard starts empty and walks
# you through setup.
#
# Want to pre-fill setup from env instead (IaC, or restoring an exported config)?
# See .env.example for the full annotated list of every seedable variable.
###############################################################################

# DEM_SECRET_KEY — root of trust for encrypting stored secrets; CANNOT live in
#   the DB it decrypts. The value below is a throwaway DEV key so the stack boots
#   on copy. Generate a fresh one for any real deployment with:
#     python -c "from cryptography.fernet import Fernet; print(Fernet.generate_key().decode())"
# DATABASE_URL — job/state + config store. SQLite (file in the conductor_data
#   volume) by default; Postgres for servers: postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@db/dem
DEM_SECRET_KEY=KZuEczTWuN0bKeiUYVY6q8JDT6mMSYwX48d3g8RRqms=
DATABASE_URL=sqlite+aiosqlite:////data/conductor.db
